---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { Icon } from 'astro-icon/components';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Remnant Inventory Monetization for Publishers | AdBunny"
  description="Fill unsold ad slots with AdBunny. One JS tag, AI-optimized banner selection, zero conflict with your existing ad stack. Start monetizing today."
  keywords="remnant inventory monetization for publishers, unsold ad space, fill rate optimization, backfill ad monetization, monetize website traffic, banner ad revenue"
>
<section class="page-header">
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Monetize Every Impression Your Current Stack Doesn't Fill</h1>
    <p>If you're running direct deals or header bidding, you already know some percentage of your inventory goes unsold or fills at a discount. AdBunny catches that gap. One JS tag, AI-optimized backfill, and revenue starts flowing from slots that used to sit empty.</p>
    <div class="hero-actions" style="margin-top:2rem;justify-content:center;">
      <a href="/" class="btn btn-primary">Get Your JS Tag</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="two-col">
      <div class="col-text">
        <span class="label">The Problem</span>
        <h2>The Remnant Inventory Problem</h2>
        <p>Even well-optimized ad stacks leave impressions on the table — geos with thin demand, times of day with low bid density, slots outside your top placements. Traditionally, publishers deal with this using a fixed waterfall: call network A, then B, then C, in a set order, regardless of what's actually the best-paying option for that specific impression. It's simple, but it leaves revenue behind.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-visual">
        <img src="/images/publisher-conveyor.png" alt="Analogy: second smart nozzle fills bottles the main nozzle missed — like AdBunny fills remnant slots">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-alt">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="label">How It Works</span>
    <h2 class="section-title">How AdBunny Fills the Gap</h2>
    <div class="grid-3">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-icon"><Icon name="lucide:layers" /></div>
        <h3>Sits below your primary stack</h3>
        <p>AdBunny is a backfill layer, not a replacement. It only evaluates inventory your existing direct deals and header bidding partners didn't fill.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-icon"><Icon name="lucide:bot" /></div>
        <h3>AI picks the best banner per impression</h3>
        <p>Instead of a static call order, AdBunny's optimization layer evaluates real-time demand for each individual impression and serves whichever banner is likely to pay the most.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-icon"><Icon name="lucide:plug" /></div>
        <h3>One tag, no dev lift</h3>
        <p>No line items to configure, no waterfall to maintain, no new SDK for your engineering team to integrate. Paste the tag, done.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="label">What You Get</span>
    <h2 class="section-title">What You Get</h2>
    <div class="grid-3">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Higher fill rate on remnant slots</h3>
        <p>AI-driven yield optimization instead of a static, out-of-date waterfall.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Zero interference with primary demand</h3>
        <p>No conflict with your existing direct-sold or header-bidding demand.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Same-day setup</h3>
        <p>One tag, no ad-ops overhead, no engineering sprint required.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-alt">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="label">Who It's For</span>
    <h2 class="section-title">Who This Is For</h2>
    <p class="section-sub">Publishers and app developers of any size dealing with unsold or underperforming banner inventory — from independent sites supplementing a small ad stack to larger publishers looking to squeeze more yield out of remnant slots without adding ad-ops overhead.</p>
    <div class="col-visual">
      <img src="/images/hero-umbrella.png" alt="Analogy: second umbrella catching rain — like AdBunny catches remnant revenue">
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section-cta">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Your Remnant Inventory Is Worth More Than It's Earning</h2>
    <p>See what AI-optimized backfill can do for your fill rate.</p>
    <a href="/" class="btn btn-primary">Get Your JS Tag</a>
  </div>
</section>
</BaseLayout>
